Date: 1998-03-15

Title: Creation of Closed or Open Universe from Constrained Instanton

Authors: Z.C. Wu (Beijing Normal University)

Comments: 5 pages, modified

Journal-ref: Gen.Rel.Grav. 30 (1998) 1639

In the no-boundary univers e the universe is created from an instanton.However, there does not exist any instanton for the ``realistic'' $FRW$universe with a scalar field. The ``instanton'' leading to its quantum creationmay be modified and reinterpreted as a constrained gravitational instanton.